“ A farmer wants to cross a river and take with him a dog, a chicken and a basket of veggies.”
1. The farmer is the only one who can sail the boat. He can only take one passenger, in addition to himself. 2. The dog can harm the chicken and the chicken can eat the veggies 3. You can not leave any two crossers on the same bank if they can harm each other
How can the farmer get across the river with all the 2 animals and the plant without any losses?
